An Act relative to retirement benefits for Alec Ciminello.
Whereas, The deferred operation of this act would tend to defeat its purpose, which is to
to establish forthwith creditable service for Alec Ciminello, therefore it is hereby declared to be
an emergency law, therefore it is hereby declared to be an emergency law, necessary for the
immediate preservation of the public convenience.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Notwithstanding chapter 32 of the General Laws or any other general or special law to
2 the contrary, the teachers’ retirement system shall credit Alec Ciminello, a member of the
3 teachers’ retirement system, with 7.92 years of creditable service for the teaching service he
4 rendered in Rhode Island for the period of August 1, 2014 through June 30, 2022, inclusive, for
5 the purpose of determining his superannuation retirement allowance pursuant to paragraph (a) of
6 subdivision (2) of section 5 of said chapter 32. Before the date that any retirement allowance
7 becomes effective for Alec Ciminello, he shall pay into the annuity savings fund of the teachers’
8 retirement system in 1 sum or in installments, upon such terms and conditions as the teachers’
9 retirement board may prescribe, an amount equal to that which would have been withheld as
